THURSDAY PUZZLE — We’re over the hump of the week and cruising toward the weekend, so no long faces. Even if you’re having a “meh” week, we have at least two reasons to smile.

While today’s puzzle does not have the Thursday high-wire tricks we’ve come to expect, Alan Arbesfeld’s offering is relatively easy and should allow even new solvers to experience a degree of success.

Mr. Arbesfeld has also spent some time remaking movies to give them more uplifting titles. If you hang out on Twitter, this theme might feel familiar: It’s the game people play where they change a word to make a different phrase. This one might be given the hashtag #makeamoviemoreuplifting.

Today’s Theme

Mr. Arbesfeld offers us four movie titles that are kind of lackluster and changes a word to make each a bit happier. For example, at 26A, the “Uplifting remake of a 2010 Annette Bening/Julianne Moore film?” is based on the movie “The Kids Are All Right” and is remade as THE KIDS ARE SUPER.

Advertisement Continue reading the main story

Similarly, and this was my favorite of the bunch, at 51A, the “Uplifting remake of a 1964 Audrey Hepburn/Rex Harrison film?” is based on “My Fair Lady” and is remade as MY AWESOME LADY.
