Dear New Jerseyans,

Do you have a question you’d like to ask your next governor before the election on Nov. 7? Perhaps it’s a statewide problem that you encounter every day — maybe it’s about schools, jobs or health care. Or maybe it’s more specific, like your commute to work, legalizing marijuana or your property taxes.

We want to gather readers’ questions in hopes of getting responses for you — yes, you.

This race — its two leading candidates are Philip D. Murphy, a Democrat, and Lt. Gov. Kim Guadagno, a Republican — marks the end of Gov. Chris Christie’s tumultuous tenure and has the potential to shift the governor’s seat from red to blue.

